translated: Forssell, Greta, dentist, Gothenburg, born September 28, 1908 in Gothenburg to merchant Håkan Leffler and dentist Svea Rune. Married in 1936 to civil engineer Sigvard Fors-seiLl. Children: see him. - Studied for the final examinations in Vänersborg in 1928, dentistry 1929, and received a degree in dentistry in 1932. Practiced in Brålanda from 1933-1935, substitute dentist in the Gothenburg Municipal Dental Clinic and Gothenburg School Dental Clinic in 1936 and 1937, and a regular dentist in the latter in 1938. From 1940-1941, assistant dentist at the Eastman Institute in Stockholm, school dentist in the Gothenburg School Dental Clinic in 1942, and regular since 1945. Wrote a critique of modern Swedish obstetric care, with a proposal for inspection in writing to the King in 1944, included in the Report of the Population Committee in 1945, and presented to Parliament in 1947. Also wrote articles on children's dental care, child rearing, and maternal care in newspapers and journals.
